#HELPS

-1 'RACE HELP' 'RACE' 'RACES'~
The following are the selectable PC races available on Distortions of Chaos.

Avian		Bastet		Centaur		Demon
Draconian	Drow		Dwarf		Eladrin
Elf		Ent		Fireling	Gnoll
Gnome		Goblin		Gryphon		Halfelf
Halfling	Halforc		Heucuva		Howler
Human		Iceling		Illithid	Imp
Kitsune		Kuo-Toa		Lupine		Minotaur
Mutant		Nymph		Obsidimen	Ogre
Phoenix		Pixie		Satyr		Shade
Shockling	Thri-Kreen	Titan		Troll

Each race has an individual help file with detailed information. Please see
those for more information on the specific races.   ( Example: Help Human )

Attributes listed in the individual help files are listed at their maximum
trainable value without taking class into consideration. An additional two
points can be added to the primary attribute for the character's class.
~

-1 Avian~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 21/Wis 22/Dex 22/Con 19
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Lightning
Vulnerabilities : Poison, Disease
Racial Affects  : Flying, Farsight
Racial Abilities: None

A race of strange bird-like humanoids, the origin of the Avian species is unknown
though many have speculated elven or gryphon heritage. While most stand nearly as
tall as humans, there is great variety among the various Avian varieties. Feather
coloration, height, and wingspan differs from region to region.  While not strong
or remarkably hearty, Avian are known for the quick reflexes and keen eyes and as
such make decent assassins.
~

-1 Bastet~
Max Attributes  : Str 18/Int 20/Wis 15/Dex 24/Con 18
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Mental, Earth
Vulnerabilities : Charm, Sound
Racial Affects  : Haste, Infrared
Racial Abilities: None

It has long been rumored that a race of catlike people was born of a long-forgotten
goddess. Few who have seen members of this elusive race describe any two similarly.
Some are rumored to be shapeshifters who can assume a human-like form with telltale
signs of their feline heritage, but who can change into cats of different sizes.  A
few have told of humanoids with the heads and tails of cats. Some are said to stalk
about in the darkness, while others are reported to love basking in sunlight. Which
of the rumors are true is unknown to all but the Bastet, the children of an ancient
goddess.  All the tales, however, hold two things true: these cat-people are always
fast as lightning with a wit just as quick.
~

-1 Centaur~
Max Attributes  : Str 22/Int 16/Wis 20/Dex 20/Con 22
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Nature
Vulnerabilities : Energy, Negative
Racial Affects  : Detect Hidden
Racial Abilities: Enhanced Damage

Strong and sturdy, Centaurs are a strange race with the upper torso of a human which
rises from the body of a horse. Forest dwellers by nature, many centaurs tend toward
the profession of tracker or strider, guarding the woods they call home.  Others are
famed for the skill in battle, while some have taken to studying the movement of the
stars and the mechanisations of nature herself.  Even the most brutish centaurs seem
to possess a deep understanding and appreciation for nature and a practical wisdom.
~

-1 Demon Demon-race 'demon race'~
Max Attributes  : Str 24/Int 15/Wis 15/Dex 24/Con 22
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Energy, Negative
Vulnerabilities : Holy, Silver
Racial Affects  : Frenzy, Haste, Detect Good
Racial Abilities: Berserk

Born of the darkest pits of Hell, demons are beings of hatred and destruction.
They come in a variety of forms, from grotesque clawed beasts, to suave ebony-
skinned overlords, to decadent succubi.   Their motives are as varied as their
physicalities.  Some kill for the sheer pleasure while others may serve one of
the many devil lords of hell, and yet others keep their reasons to themselves.
One thing unites all demons:  the war their homeland constantly wages with the
heavens. Demons and Eladrin will be eternally at odds, darkness forever at war
with the light.
~

-1 Draconian~
Max Attributes  : Str 23/Int 20/Wis 16/Dex 18/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Bash, Charm
Vulnerabilities : Pierce
Racial Affects  : Flying
Racial Abilities: None

A strange crossbreed of humanoid species and dragons, the draconian are scaled
like their larger parent and bear large wings capable of limited flight.  They
walk upright like their bipedal parents, their form resembling that of humans.
They are well muscled and healthy, often snobbish feeling they are of superior
mind and body to other humanoids. While most Draconian will remain as such all
their lives, some have found a way to free themselves of their humanoid bodies
and transform into great dragons.  The process is said to be difficult and has
been kept a guarded secret by those few who have discovered it.

{RSPECIAL{W:{x Draconians are the only race which may evolve into dragons.
         See {YHelp Dragon{x for more information.
~

-1 Dragon~
Dragons, as a Player Character race, are not currently available. Eventually,
we intend to permit draconian characters to spend IQP and RP points to evolve
into dragons, but the system is not yet finished.  When it is, they will have
the opportunity to choose from different types of dragons (generally speaking
these will be standard D&D dragon colors) each with their own resistances and
vulnerabilites, as well as a breath weapon. This file will be updated as soon
as the changes are in to include the cost of evolution, as well as statistics
for each dragon type available.
~

-1 Drow drow-race~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 21/Wis 16/Dex 24/Con 16
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Charm, Negative, Poison
Vulnerabilities : Iron, Light
Racial Affects  : Hide, Infrared
Racial Abilities: Sneak, Dodge

Hailing from the depths of the world come the drow, darkest of the elven races.
Most drow deny their relation to the surface elves but it's difficult to ignore
the physical similarities such as angular faces and sharply pointed ears.  Drow
society is primarily matriarchal with a rich background in magical arts.  Their
priesthood abounds, though compared to other races of the realms, their priests
are not nearly as impressive as their sorcerers and assassins.  Ever-suspicious
and remarkably cunning, a drow's intellect and speed are her greatest asset.
~

-1 Dwarf~
Max Attributes  : Str 23/Int 18/Wis 18/Dex 16/Con 25
Immunities      : Poison
Resistances     : Disease, Earth
Vulnerabilities : Water
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: Berserk

A short and stocky race hailing from mountainous regions, Dwarves tend to be the
most hearty of all known races, able to resist disease and outdrink anyone. They
possess a long history and a rich culture, full of what the other races consider
some of the finest stone and metalwork and some of the driest tomes of genealogy
found in all of the realms.  Dwarves are known to anger quickly, a fine asset in
battle, but a poor quality in diplomats. However, they are a well-rounded people
and tend toward all manner of professions.
~

-1 Eladrin~
Max Attributes  : Str 18/Int 20/Wis 23/Dex 18/Con 21
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Holy, Light
Vulnerabilities : Iron, Negative
Racial Affects  : Flying, Bless, Detect Evil
Racial Abilities: Continual Light

Eladrin are beings born of light who live in the Heavens.  Most resemble humans
of unearthly beauty with a pair of snow white wings set in their backs. They're
a wise and compassionate race built to guide the earth-dwelling races and fight
the corruptive forces of Hell.  Their great wisdom lends them to superb healing
abilities and understanding of the world,  leading many Eladrin to the paths of
priest or sage. Many, however, are armed as knights to fight in the eternal war
against darkness, demon-slaying their primary goal.
~

-1 Elf~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 25/Wis 20/Dex 23/Con 16
Immunities      : Charm
Resistances     : Silver
Vulnerabilities : Iron
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: Sneak, Hide

One of the most long-lived races, elves are known for the keen intellects, ageless
wisdom and exotic beauty. They possess sharply pointed ears and angled eyes; their
cheekbones are high set, their complexions clear. Their lithe bodies are work well
at archery and light swordplay.  Their extensive studies and sharp minds make them
fine wizards.  Though elven cultures vary across the realms as greatly as do human
ones, most elven societies know the secret to creating a finely woven chainmail as
light as a feather and tough as steel.  
~

-1 Ent~
Max Attributes  : Str 20/Int 17/Wis 23/Dex 12/Con 23
Immunities      : Wood
Resistances     : Nature
Vulnerabilities : Fire, Lightning
Racial Affects  : Briarshield
Racial Abilities: None

The origin of ents is much debated.  So old is the race that even they have greatly
forgotten their true begining. Some believe that the ents were born of the earth as
trees and were blessed with sentience and mobility by strong elven magics and asked
to guard the forests.  This seems as reasonable an explanation as any.  Ents appear
to be the largest and oldest of any variety of trees, tall and slow.  They are made
of wood-like flesh which permits them strength, but not speed.  Their long lives in
the forests tend to cultivate within them great wisdom and health and many practice
nature-based magic and healing arts.
~

-1 Fireling~
Max Attributes  : Str 22/Int 18/Wis 14/Dex 22/Con 19
Immunities      : Fire
Resistances     : Wood
Vulnerabilities : Cold, Water
Racial Affects  : Fireshield, Dark Vision
Racial Abilities: Fast healing

Descended from fire elementals, Firelings resemble bronze-skinned humans with flames
dancing in their eyes.  Heat radiates from their bodies and their skin is hot to the
touch. Strong and fast, Firelings can be powerful adversaries. They tend to be quick 
with a clever quip, but also quick to anger.  The fire which burns inside them fuels
a strong temper and sharp mind.
~

-1 Gnoll~
Max Attributes  : Str 20/Int 15/Wis 15/Dex 23/Con 20
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Charm
Vulnerabilities : Poison
Racial Affects  : Berserk, Dark Vision
Racial Abilities: None

Small, dog-like humanoids, gnolls have long been a slave-race.  Others have abused
them due to their small size and low intelligence.  Recent generations have proved
stronger than their forebearers,  using their size and speed to their advantage as
they fought for their freedom. Now, they keep to themselves, working on developing
their own culture and afraid that the other races might try to enslave them again.
They abhor slavery in any form as they  have suffered the brunt of it for too many
generations.  Solitary gnolls often take to thievery to make their living as there
is little else beyond manual labor at which they excel.
~

-1 Gnome~
Max Attributes  : Str 15/Int 24/Wis 22/Dex 23/Con 16
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Acid, Mental
Vulnerabilities : Cold, Disease
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: None

Though one of the more common races, gnomes only seem to adventure infrequently.
Most prefer to stay among their own kind, engaging in alchemical experiments and
wordplay.  Those who venture out tend toward trickery, though not always in very
malicious ways, favoring illusion and stealth to more direct forms of combat. It
is common knowledge that gnomes pick names for themselves which they think sound
interesting or exciting.  They also pick names for each other.  Most gnomes have
gathered such greatly long names that they only offer the first few syllables to
members of other races to avoid confusion, though some of the more sadistic will
insist others call them by their full name.
~

-1 Goblin~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 22/Wis 16/Dex 23/Con 20
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Cold
Vulnerabilities : Light
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: Sneak

These small, mountain-dwelling creatures are commonly thought to be as dumb as
the rocks they live among, but goblins tend to be far more clever than many of
the subterranean races.  Their quick minds and quicker reflexes make them very
capable thieves and mercenaries, though most humanoids prefer to avoid contact
with these creatures. Most often, their skin is a greyish green and their eyes
are black and beady.  They don't generally trust others as goblins have been a
target of most other races for as long as they can remember.  Perhaps it's the
tradition of theft and raiding that others dislike so much.
~

-1 Gryphon~
Max Attributes  : Str 18/Int 23/Wis 23/Dex 18/Con 18
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Light, Lightning
Vulnerabilities : Earth, Water
Racial Affects  : Flying, Farsight
Racial Abilities: None

Great beings built with the body of a lion and the head, beak, and wings of an
eagle, Gryphons are imposing to say the least. They are said to build nests of
gold and have a keen insight into the locations of buried treasures. Born from
large eggs, gryphons are often raised high in the mountains, isolated from the
rest of the world.  The few outsiders they see are often treasure hunters come
to steal the gold from their nests; therefore, gryphons commonly have a strong
distaste for the other races.  Gryphons are even more impressive mentally than
physically, making them skilled in all pursuits.
~

-1 Halfelf~
Max Attributes  : Str 17/Int 23/Wis 19/Dex 20/Con 18
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Charm, Silver
Vulnerabilities : None
Racial Affects  : Farsight
Racial Abilities: Hide

Most often the product of relationships or rapes between elves and humans,
half-elves have no society or culture of their own. To the elves, they are
human, while to the human they are elves. Most feel they have no true home
and no ties beyond family to either culture.   This drives many half-elves
to live a nomadic lifestyle and spawned many a fine adventurer.  The elven
heritage permits them a fine intellect and dexterity, while the human side
gives them more versatility.  
~

-1 Halfling~
Max Attributes  : Str 15/Int 16/Wis 18/Dex 24/Con 24
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Poison, Disease
Vulnerabilities : None
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: Sneak

When halflings are around, it is wise to keep watch on both your wallet and
your dinner plate.  They are known for their sleight of hand and their love
of good food.  Most also come with a tale or two... or twelve.   Boisterous
when they want to be, halflings can also be stealthy when they choose. Many
halflings who have ventured away from  the comfort of their kitchens become
rather successful thieves and assassins.
~

-1 Halforc~
Max Attributes  : Str 21/Int 16/Wis 15/Dex 20/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Weapon
Vulnerabilities : Acid, Mental
Racial Affects  : Berserk
Racial Abilities: None

Like the half-elves, half-orcs are a product of cross-breeding, though more
often than not, their conception was forceful. Even within the society they
are raised, be it human or orc, they are seen as outsiders and often merely
tolerated for their mother's sake.  They tend to be strong and healthy, but
lacking in intellect and understanding.   Most learn pretty early on how to
fight for themselves, and many pick up a blade and take to adventuring at a
young age.
~

-1 Heucuva~
Max Attributes  : Str 25/Int 10/Wis 10/Dex 25/Con 25
Immunities      : Poison, Disease
Resistances     : Slash, Pierce, Negative
Vulnerabilities : Bash, Charm, Holy, Silver
Racial Affects  : Dark Vision
Racial Abilities: Second Attack

Of all undead known to the realms, heucuva are among the strongest, toughest,
and fastest.  While they may resembles skeletons with very little flesh still
clinging to their bones, heucuvas tend to be much more formiddable opponents.
How they are created is often debated.  Some claim they were priests who were
corrupt; they were forsaken by their gods, cursed, and barred from death.  It
has also been suggested that they were created by a powerful necromancer, who
was eventually slaughtered at the hands of his own minions. Either way, these
grotesque beings are a physical match for most foes, but they greatly lack an
intellect or free will of their own. Many seek to become soldiers or servants
of powerful organizations, finding life under another's command natural.
~

-1 Howler~
Max Attributes  : Str 21/Int 16/Wis 18/Dex 22/Con 18
Immunities      : Sound
Resistances     : Cold
Vulnerabilities : Disease, Light
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: Howl

It is speculated that howlers are a mutation of goblins, smaller and stronger,
but lacking the wit their cousins possess.   Howlers spend most of their lives
under ground, their sensitive eyes accustomed to the dark.  Little is known of
their strange society, but they are known to be cautious and avoid all contact
with outsiders.  Some, however, have ventured into the light of the surface to
become adventurers.  Their guarded nature is well-suited for supportive roles,
such as healer or rogue.  Howlers have been given  their name by surfacers due
to the painful screeching howl the small creatures can emit.
~

-1 Human~
Max Attributes  : Str 19/Int 19/Wis 19/Dex 19/Con 19
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : None
Vulnerabilities : None
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: None

Most populous of all the races, humans are also the most versatile.  They adapt
well to most situations and are capable in any profession they choose.  Much of
the land's heroic legends revolve around human adventurers,  though this may be
due to the fact that most of those tales have been told by humans. While humans
are not particular strong in any one area, they also do not any possess obvious
exploitable weaknesses.
~

-1 Iceling~
Max Attributes  : Str 20/Int 16/Wis 22/Dex 14/Con 23
Immunities      : Cold
Resistances     : Water
Vulnerabilities : Fire
Racial Affects  : Iceshield
Racial Abilities: Fast healing

Descended from elemental ice, Icelings resemble humans with pale skin and chilly
blue or grey eyes.  They tend to be patient and calculating, taking in the whole
picture before reacting. Strong of will and body, Icelings make superior priests
and warriors, bringing deliberate grace to all they do. They view the world from
a detached perspective, feeling little stir in their cold hearts.  Their bodies,
like their minds, are cool and clean.
~

-1 Illithid~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 25/Wis 21/Dex 18/Con 15
Immunities      : Mental
Resistances     : None
Vulnerabilities : Slash
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: Psionic Blast, Meditation

Most other races find illithids appalling, which is fine by them as they see the
other races as little more than potential slaves. Using their superior intellect
and psionic abilities, illithids dominate and destroy the inferior,  weak-minded
races.  They feast upon the brains of others, thus giving rise to the derogatory
epitaph mind flayers.  The illithids don't see this as a bad thing.  Very seldom
do any illithids stray from their own kind, leaving the hive mentality and over-
mind behind.  Many have a difficult time adjusting to thinking as an individual,
without all its brethren's thoughts joining it.  Physically, illithids are lanky
and tall with pasty grey skin. Their skulls are elongated and where their mouths
would be are four tentacles.  Genders are indistinguishable if not non-existent.
~

-1 Imp~
Max Attributes  : Str 14/Int 23/Wis 17/Dex 23/Con 18
Immunities      : Poison
Resistances     : Magic
Vulnerabilities : Charm, Holy, Acid
Racial Affects  : Haste, Flying
Racial Abilities: Hide

Smart and fast, imps are unrepentent pranksters. Many imps tend toward malicious
deeds, leaving the victims of their jokes in pain, anger, anguish, or all three.
Most imps stand less than one foot tall, though there is plenty of variety among
the several impish species. Imps are native to hell and may be related to demons
who also reside in those depths.  As imps are often summoned by wizards, they've
developed a strong resistance to magics, though they are often weak to the charm
spells which keep them service-bound.  Imps often rival the summoning wizards in
intellect and ability, and thus resent such imprisonment.
~

-1 Kitsune~
Max Attributes  : Str 15/Int 24/Wis 21/Dex 22/Con 15
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Charm, Fire
Vulnerabilities : Water
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: None

The term sly as a fox applies to the kitsune in more way than one.  Not only do
the possess the swift intellect attributed to the creatures, but they also have
their blood within them.  A rare and magical race, the kitsune often seem to be
merely human to most, but if one looks closely, there is a touch of mischief in
their eyes that belies their true nature. Many associate these fox-kin with the
element of fire, perhaps because most (though not all) have reddish hair. There
may be some truth to this for nearly all kitsune have a fear of water.
~

-1 Kuo-Toa~
Max Attributes  : Str 15/Int 21/Wis 25/Dex 15/Con 19
Immunities      : Water
Resistances     : Mental, Poison
Vulnerabilities : Cold, Lightning
Racial Affects  : Swim
Racial Abilities: Wspit, Meditation

An amphibian race with a strange, tribal society, Kuo-Toa are known for the
potency of their priesthood.  Their squat bodies and long arms are not made
for combat, though they certainly are capable when necessary.  Instead, the
Kuo-Toa focus their studies on the divine and arcane arts, often discussing
the finer points of religion and philosophy for days on end. While they are
a primarily peaceful society, the Kuo-Toa will fiercely defend their family
and home with potent magics and finely crafted spears when necessary.
~

-1 Lupine~
Max Attributes  : Str 22/Int 16/Wis 14/Dex 22/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Iron, Slash
Vulnerabilities : Pierce, Silver
Racial Affects  : Infrared
Racial Abilities: Howl

Half man and half wolf, lupine are strong and fierce.  The origins of these
hybrids is uncertain, but many view it as a curse which expresses itself in
many ways. Some, it is said, are able to alternate their form, appearing as
a man one day and a wolf the next.  Others, however, are caught between the
two, forever expressing both human and wolflike traits. This latter variety
is suspected to be the progeny of the prior.  Physically, lupines possess a
great bit of stength and often use this to their advantage, finding work as
soldiers or mercenaries.
~

-1 Minotaur~
Max Attributes  : Str 24/Int 16/Wis 15/Dex 17/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Bash, Slash
Vulnerabilities : Energy, Mental
Racial Affects  : Farsight
Racial Abilities: Enhanced Damage

Minotaurs are undeniably among the most  powerful fighters in the land.  They
are trained in combat from their youth and possess military prowess which far
outweighs most other societies.  Their bodies resemble those of strong, well-
muscled humans, while their heads are those of bulls, often bearing two large
horns.  While other professions exist within minotaur society, a majority are
trained as fine warriors.
~

-1 Mutant~
Max Attributes  : Str 22/Int 15/Wis 15/Dex 18/Con 25
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Acid, Sound
Vulnerabilities : Slash
Racial Affects  : Acidshield
Racial Abilities: None

Many speculate that mutants began as the subjects of magical and alchemical
experiments who were tossed aside and forgotten--or perhaps freed--by their
masters.  Exposure to large varieties of chemicals  and frequent explosions
has left them resistant to acids and a little hard of hearing.  The changes
seem to carry over into subsequent generations. They also possess a strange
toxic aura, making them unwelcome in most societies. Their twisted features
don't exactly make them well-liked either. Their skin is thin, sometimes to
the point of translucency.  Physically, however, they can withstand quite a
beating as well as give one.  An angered mutant is something to fear.
~

-1 Nymph~
Max Attributes  : Str 16/Int 20/Wis 23/Dex 18/Con 18
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Nature
Vulnerabilities : Negative, Slash
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: Charm Person

Nymphs are the spirits of nature, the physical personifications of the woods
and the mountains, the lakes and the ocean. They are radiantly beautiful and
possess such allure that most are unable to resist any request they make.  A
nymph will weaken if kept from her home, or one like it, for too long.  Most
nymphs are female, though a rare male has existed.  It is said that they are
born directly from the spirit of the earth, but given their seductive nature
most dismiss that rumor.
~

-1 Obsidimen~
Max Attributes  : Str 25/Int 18/Wis 20/Dex 10/Con 22
Immunities      : Earth
Resistances     : Weapon
Vulnerabilities : Acid, Energy, Sound
Racial Affects  : Stone Skin
Racial Abilities: None

It is rare indeed to see an obsidimen far from the mountains for they are part
of the stone from which they are born. Within the mountain they call home, the
obsidimen are able to communicate freely with their brethren.  However, if one
leaves, it finds itself alone with its thoughts.  Obsidimen are massive, their
bodies made from living stone.  They possess no genders, for they have no need
of such means of reproduction.  Some, however, feel the need to associate with
one gender or the other when entering into other societies.  Obsidimen possess
unmatched patience and take their time in everything they do.  This makes them
fine craftsmen and excellent scholars.

[Note: This race was blatantly stolen from Earthdawn and modified for DoC.]
~

-1 Ogre~
Max Attributes  : Str 23/Int 15/Wis 15/Dex 20/Con 22
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Weapon
Vulnerabilities : Charm, Mental, Silver
Racial Affects  : Berserk
Racial Abilities: None

Ogres are large generally ugly bipeds with thick yellowish or greenish skin and
poor hygeine.  Most view ogres as big and dumb, finding them easily influenced.
Often ogre tribes can be found in the employ of somebody who needs grunts to do
their dirty work. Ogres do, however, have their own rich culture which includes
a long history of shamanistic magic.  Though not as potent as other mages, ogre
mages are certainly to be feared, for they are competent in physical and arcane
combat.  More fearsome, however, is a frenzied ogre barbarian.
~

-1 Phoenix~
Max Attributes  : Str 15/Int 23/Wis 23/Dex 21/Con 15
Immunities      : Fire
Resistances     : Magic
Vulnerabilities : Earth, Water
Racial Affects  : Fireshield, Flying
Racial Abilities: None

Frail beings of fire, the phoenix are one of the most rare and elusive races.
Though they are birds, phoenix eggs are a true rarity as very few are born of
normal unions. Instead the race survives through a cycle of death and rebirth
which all phoenix undergo.  When a phoenix dies, it is consumed by flames and
from the remaining ashes, a new phoenix arises.   Most phoenix are remarkably
intelligent and possess the wisdom of many generations. Magic courses through
their very core, and thus they are quite skilled in casting.
~

-1 Pixie~
Max Attributes  : Str 12/Int 23/Wis 21/Dex 23/Con 16
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Magic, Light
Vulnerabilities : Bash, Sound
Racial Affects  : Flying, Detect Magic, Detect Hidden, Detect Invis
Racial Abilities: Faerie Fire

Pixies are small winged creatures with heads too large for their bodies. They
have pointed ears and noses and arched eyebrows. Their wings are translucent,
and rarely stop fluttering.  Most pixies find it tough to stay still and move
about at an alarmingly fast pace.  While generally friendly, pixies are often
extremely capricious and given to mischief.  Magic is second nature to pixies
who possess inate powers,  such as the ability to surround their enemies in a
bright outline, making the target easier to hit.
~

-1 Satyr~
Max Attributes  : Str 19/Int 16/Wis 24/Dex 18/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Nature
Vulnerabilities : Charm, Iron, Negative
Racial Affects  : Detect Good, Detect Evil, Detect Hidden
Racial Abilities: None

Satyrs dwell in the forests and revel in the beauty of nature in all its many
forms, especially the forms of the more beautiful races.  The lower body of a
satyr is covered in fur ranging from reddish brown to black, possessing a set
of legs, a tail, and hooved feet like a goat. Their upper bodies, though, are
generally human-like in form, often fit and well-toned. Satyr society centers
around revelry, sexuality, and philosophy. They are known for their endurance
in combat, drinking, and love-making, as well as their ability to debate such
things as philosophy and theology with the best minds of other cultures.
~

-1 Shade~
