It is difficult to tell a shade from a normal shadow.  Shades are beings made
of darkness itself and are thus difficult to touch or harm physically.  Their
figures are humanoid,  and while other races find it difficult to distinguish
one shade from another, shades themselves never have any such trouble.  Their
very nature, that of shadow and grace,  lends itself well to the darker sides
of combat. Shades are known for their fine assassins.  Their clergy, dark and
quiet, are also gaining notariety for their fine understanding of divine arts
and the darker side of the gods.  
~

-1 Shockling~
Max Attributes  : Str 22/Int 16/Wis 14/Dex 24/Con 19
Immunities      : Lightning
Resistances     : Energy
Vulnerabilities : Earth
Racial Affects  : Shockshield
Racial Abilities: Fast Healing

Descended from lightning elementals, shocklings resemble humans with golden
skin and glittering eyes.  Electricity sparks along their skin, making them
easily distinguishable from humans.  They are fantastically fast and nearly
as strong.  They are quick to anger, often simply because they enjoy having
the opportunity to display their combat prowess.
~

-1 Thri-Kreen~
Max Attributes  : Str 23/Int 14/Wis 14/Dex 24/Con 20
Immunities      : Acid
Resistances     : Poison
Vulnerabilities : Bash
Racial Affects  : None
Racial Abilities: Poison

The insectoid thri-kreen make their homes in the deserts of the land, hunting
whatever creatures are foolish enough to cross into their domain. Many others
see their culture as primitive and view the mantis-like thri-kreen as savages
unfit for more evolved society. The thri-kreen are more likely to act quickly
and decisively than others, prefering a direct solution to problems and swift
death for their enemies.  Their bodies are covered with tough exoskeleton and
their faces bear wicked mandibles.  Their eyes seem cold and emotionless, and
their language of clicks and trills sounds harsh to outsiders.  Being hunters
by nature, each thri-kreen thinks of himself as a loner, making interpersonal
relations difficult to say the least.  
~

-1 Titan~
Max Attributes  : Str 25/Int 16/Wis 16/Dex 16/Con 24
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : Bash, Lightning
Vulnerabilities : Energy
Racial Affects  : Farsight, Detect Invis
Racial Abilities: None

Physically, titans are one of the most imposing races in the land.  They tower
over everyone else, save maybe a few elder dragons. They tend to love war, for
it is where their skill lies. When a titan sets off on his own, it is often in
search for new opponents, others with which he can test his skills. The titans
claim to have existed before the gods  and often insist that they are the ones
who should be in power.  Whether this is true or not, only the gods know.
~

-1 Troll~
Max Attributes  : Str 25/Int 13/Wis 13/Dex 16/Con 23
Immunities      : None
Resistances     : None
Vulnerabilities : Fire
Racial Affects  : Regeneration
Racial Abilities: Berserk, Fast Healing

Trolls are hideous humanoids usually standing about eight feet tall. Their size
and strength make them formidable opponents, but it is their natural ability to
regenerate that makes them truly fearsome. Trolls have their own tribal society
which is run by the strongest of each clan. As they lack in intellect, strength
is they only true quality of worth to a troll.  If you are found weak, the clan
might break off your horns and banish you, a far more severe punishment than to
simply slay you. Some say that trolls possess a depth of spirit that others can
not comprehend, from which they find their passion for battle.   Most, however,
dismiss this claim, finding trolls to be little more than overgrown brutes.
~

